The paper proposes a method for learning a state representation from demonstration data using a multi-head neural network. This involves imitation learning and transfer learning, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on a simulated robotic arm performing a reaching task, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The input data is noisy images, which suggests the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with control tasks, which can be considered a subfield of systems and control (cs.SY).
